1 Section 2. Section 33-17-1602, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "33-17-1602. Surety bail bond insurance license -- basic course of training -- temporary
3 license. (1) Except as otherwise provided in this section, an applicant for a surety bail bond insurance license
4 shall satisfactorily complete a basic course of training for bail enforcement agents that is approved by the
5 commissioner.
6 (2) Before approving an application for a surety bail bond insurance license, the commissioner
7 shall verify that the individual:
8 (a) holds a high school diploma, general equivalency diploma, or equivalent; and
9 (b) has no felony convictions or offenses involving dishonesty, violence, or controlled substances.
10 (3) Applicants shall complete a 16-hour basic training course that includes instruction in:
11 (a) constitutional law and civil liability;
12 (b) rights of individuals in custody;
13 (c) use of force guidelines;
14 (d) procedures for arresting and surrendering defendants;
15 (e) handling individuals with mental health or substance use challenges;
16 (f) defensive tactics;
17 (g) bail bond ethics; and
18 (h) report writing and form completion.
19 (4) Once every 2 years, licensees shall complete continuing education that includes high-quality
20 relevant instruction for:
21 (a) 1 hour on updates to state and federal laws affecting the bail industry; and
22 (b) 4 hours of approved credits on general bail industry knowledge or trends that is provided by a
23 recognized state or national bail industry association or any other approved provider.
24 (5) (a) The commissioner may issue a temporary license valid for up to 12 months, allowing
25 applicants to operate under supervision while completing training requirements. Supervision must be provided
26 by a licensed surety bail bond agent who:
27 (i) has been licensed and actively in business in Montana for at least 5 consecutive years;
